The African National Congress (ANC) is holding a virtual memorial service to honour and celebrate the life of the late Isithwalandwe/Seaparankoe Ntate Andrew Mlangeni. Link to the stream:  Mlangeni who was the last remaining Rivonia trialist died on Tuesday night at the One Military hospital in Pretoria at the age of 95. He had been admitted to the hospital after complaining of abdominal problems. His funeral service will be held at the Soweto Campus of the University of Johannesburg on Wednesday. 